## In the world of software, most everything takes longer to implement than you expect. And so it's not uncommon to accomplish less in a fixed amount of time than you hope.

### In a sentence (or list of features), define a GOOD outcome for your final project. I.e., what WILL you accomplish no matter what?
- well have a minimum of 2-3 classes per day
- about 5 or more choices a day that influence the outcome
- include a sort of meter for grades/sleep/hunger/relationships that changes based on the choices (hp bar)

### In a sentence (or list of features), define a BETTER outcome for your final project. I.e., what do you THINK you can accomplish before the final project's deadline?
- make a mini knock off of canvas so we could see how your choices effect the grades (ex: skiping class, studying)
- more choices within the day, maybe even 2 days possibly instead of one (you can unlock a second day if you do really well on the first one)
- make more panels/instances that depict actual studying, haning out with friends, etc...

### In a sentence (or list of features), define a BEST outcome for your final project. I.e., what do you HOPE to accomplish before the final project's deadline?
- more choices within the day, maybe even 2 days possibly instead of one (you can unlock a second day if you do really well on the first one)
- show every panel based on the choice, even something as simple as calling your mom or speaking to someone, basically just depict more of the choices instead of jsut saying you did it
- room cutomization/more options, pick your schedule/space, like if you say yes to studying they have the choice to pick where, etc. 
-  extra credit on certain assingments

## In a paragraph or more, outline your next steps. What new skills will you need to acquire? What topics will you need to research? If working with one of two classmates, who will do what?
New skills: master (or at least learn how to use) Renpy, take pictures of part of Temple that we might need for the background photos, and learn any new comands so that we could build the code
Research: renpy tutorials, ask our friends who are in those majors what their typical day looks like, and also use temples bullitin to see the classes we need to replicate asnd learn what people do within them
Classmate work: we usually meet in person to work on this project so we will sort of deligate the work based on how much we get done in the day, writing certaion lines of code, so one of the majors we will do together and the other ones well split up and make on our own, aslso character designs wil be split up. 
